Source: pg-ash
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/NikolayS/pg_ash

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-ash
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-ash
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, postgresql-PGVERSION, postgresql-PGVERSION-cron
Description: Active Session History for PostgreSQL implemented in SQL
  pg_ash provides Active Session History (ASH) for PostgreSQL as a pure SQL/PLpgSQL extension.
  It samples pg_stat_activity over time and stores historical wait-event data
  without requiring shared_preload_libraries.
